<topic id="enabling-the-master-files-support">
  <title>Enabling the Master Files Support</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Master Files<indexterm>Enabling</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Projects<indexterm>Master
          files<indexterm>Enabling</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> stores the <term>master files</term> in a folder located in the <xref
        href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"><uicontrol
          product="author developer editor">Project</uicontrol><uicontrol
          product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">Project Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref>,
      as the first child of the project root. The <term>Master Files Support</term> is disabled by
      default and <ph keyref="product"/> allows you to enable or disable the <term>Master Files
        Support</term> for each project you are working on.</p>
    <p product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">To enable <term>Master Files</term>
      support, select <uicontrol>Enable Master Files Support</uicontrol> from the contextual menu of
      the project root folder in the <xref href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"
          ><uicontrol>Project Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref>. </p>
    <p product="author developer editor">To enable <term>Master Files</term> support, do one of the following:<ul>
        <li>Select <uicontrol>Enable Master Files Support</uicontrol> from the <uicontrol><image
              href="../img/Settings16.png"/>Settings</uicontrol> menu in the top-right corner of the
            <xref href="../topics/using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"
              ><uicontrol>Project</uicontrol> view</xref>.</li>
        <li>Select <uicontrol>Enable Master Files Support</uicontrol> from the contextual menu of
          the project root folder in the <xref
            href="../topics/using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"
              ><uicontrol>Project</uicontrol> view</xref>. If a disabled <term>Master Files</term>
          folder exists, you can also select that option from its contextual menu.</li>
        <li>Click the <uicontrol>Enable</uicontrol> button in the tooltip located at the bottom of
          the <xref href="../topics/using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"
              ><uicontrol>Project</uicontrol> view</xref>. This tooltip window is displayed when the
            <term>Master Files</term> support is disabled. Clicking the <uicontrol>Read
            more</uicontrol> link takes you to the user guide. Clicking the
            <uicontrol>Enable</uicontrol> button opens the <uicontrol>Enable Master
            Files</uicontrol> dialog box. This dialog box contains general information about the
            <uicontrol>Master Files Support</uicontrol> and allows you to enable it. You can also
          use the <uicontrol>Detect and Enable</uicontrol> button in this dialog box to detect the
            <term>master files</term> from the current project.<note type="warning"> Once you close
            this window tip, <ph keyref="product"/> hides it for all projects. You can make the
            window tip reappear by <xref
              href="import-export-preferences.dita#import-export-preferences">resetting <ph
                keyref="product"/> to its default settings</xref>. However, doing so will result in
            you losing your customized options.</note></li>
      </ul></p>
  </body>
